 :tx/rationale "ATT-2 DEEP SPEC: HOT-COLD PATH INTERACTION. The dual-path model has three interaction points where hot-path cache data flows into cold-path datoms. INTERACTION 1 (ATT-5 Hebbian): When verbose-after-compressed is detected, main.rs reads cache.last_omitted and transacts :attention/hebbian-boost datoms for those labels. The cache provides WHICH blocks were omitted; the datoms record the LEARNING from that omission. INTERACTION 2 (ATT-6 Bayesian): When a task closes, the HL-3 pipeline looks up which blocks were presented (from cache.blocks) in recent status outputs preceding the task close. Blocks present before productive closures get weight reinforcement via :attention/learned-weight datoms. INTERACTION 3 (Composite scoring): On the NEXT status call, build_status_projection reads BOTH the cache (for surprisal = 1/sqrt(count)) AND the store (for hebbian_boost and learned_weight). The composite score is: attention = surprisal × relevance × actionability × (1 + hebbian_boost) × learned_weight. The cache provides the fast-decaying signal. The datoms provide the slow-learning signal. Together they form a dual-timescale attention system: fast habituation + slow calibration."
